radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix demonstrates wall thickening and adjacent adenopathy with trace surrounding fat stranding. An appendicolith is noted at the origin of the appendix. No drainable fluid collection. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Small hypodensities in the liver likely represent small cysts or biliary hamartomas. The stomach is moderately distended with a small duplication cyst and a small hiatal hernia. Kidneys show no focal lesion or hydronephrosis.
